<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>show a face • show one’s face</xh5><p> <i>show a face</i>—(dated) demonstrate bravery or audacity: De la Haye and Douglas were both wounded, but the little party continued to <u>show a face</u> to their foes.</p><p> <i>show one’s face</i>—(often negat.) appear somewhere, especially when one is not welcome in a place: After what she said, she had better not <u>show her face</u> around here again.</p> </entry>
